(1) Etiology + Prevention: hip flexors (iliopsoas, rectus) shorten — prone positioning prevention (15-30 min q-shift TID), avoiding prolonged sitting/supine w/ pillow under residual;

(2) Consequences: gait — excessive lordosis, vaulting, increased energy expenditure, prosthetic alignment difficulty;

(3) Assessment: Thomas test, gait analysis, ROM; goniometric measure;

(4) Treatment:
