(4) Stratification + RED-S Risk Assessment Tool (red/yellow/green);

(5) Management — multidisciplinary:
  • Sports medicine physician;
  • Sports dietitian (increase energy availability — goal);
  • Mental health/psychology + eating disorder specialist;
  • Endocrinology if hormonal;
  • Coach + family education;

(6) Treatment:
  • Increase energy availability (food intake or decrease training);
  • Treat eating disorder if present;
  • Bone health (Ca + vit D + weight-bearing + medication selected);
  • Hormonal therapy controversial — address root cause first;

(7) Training modification + return-to-sport when criteria met;

(8) Long-term monitoring; Modern: RED-S framework + multidisciplinary + early identification
