  • IRF: most intensive — high therapy + medical complexity;
  • SNF (skilled nursing): less intensive — chronic, lower-tolerance, slower-paced;
  • LTACH (long-term acute care): medically complex w/ prolonged need;
  • Home health + outpatient: lower-intensity outpatient when ready;

(4) Pre-admission screening (PAS) — comprehensive; documents IRF appropriateness;

(5) Admission process: PAS → physician concurrence → admission;

